Food and Feeding.
Dall’s Porpoises are opportunistic feeders, taking a wide variety of prey items. These include mostly mid-water and surface-living fish and cephalopods, such as herring (
Clupea
), anchovies (
Engraulis
), sardines (
Sardinops
, 
Clupeidae
), hake (Merluccius), sauries (
Cololabis
, 
Scomberesocidae
), lanternfish (
Myctophidae
), and gonatid squid (
Gonatidae
). They occasionally consume invertebrates such as krill, decapods, and various species of shrimps, but these latter items are not considered to be their primary prey.
